node.text:
⁣
I had so much fun playing in the bubbles and swimming amongst 10000 of fish. I have never seen such an abundant, healthy & thriving dive site! ⁣
⁣
I also had so much fun playing with this footage and editing it. I’d appreciate any tips or advice from those that create magical clips! 🙏🏼 💙⁣
⁣⁣⁣
“The ocean stirs the heart, inspires the imagination, & brings eternal joy to the soul” ⁣⁣⁣
-Robert Wyland ⁣⁣⁣
⁣
📹@j.kowitz⁣
⁣

node.text: This footage was taken in Mo’orea on three different days and on many different drops. Humpbacks are migrating from Antartica to mate and give birth from August until November. I was lucky enough to have not one by many encounters with these gentle giants!  My interaction was completely different each and every time I got into the water. I can't stop thinking about the past week, it was as if time was standing still. Being in the middle of the deep blue and seeing a shadow slowly move closer and closer and get larger and larger until a massive creature, one you have only seen on television and in books is coming straight towards. Not only her but with one curios one month old calf! An experience like this will give you an understanding of just how small we really are and how large our world is, and how much is still so unknown.  It gives you an appreciation for our universe. I want to find a way to make this my life! I want to explore and give back to our oceans! It was magical my friends! Let me know what you think of my video! I was smiling from ear to ear creating this piece!

Thank you, my friends!!!!! 😊😊⁣
⁣
